      "id": "962ddd99_c794b885",
      "file_path": "bpmn/so-bpmn-building-blocks/src/main/resources/subprocess/BuildingBlock/AssignPnfBB.bpmn",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 14,
      "message": "I removed CheckAaiForPnfCorrelationId as discussed above and executed suggested testcases. The results are as follows:\n(Preconditions -> Event -> Result)\n\n- Pnf does not exist in AAI -> Send a request with pnf P1 and service S1 -> P1 is created in AAI and connected to S1\n\n- Pnf P1 with a connection to service S1 exist in AAI -> Send a request with pnf P1 and service S2 -> No changes in AAI, log from bpmn-infra: multiplicity violated:multiplicity rule violated: only one edge can exist with label: org.onap.relationships.inventory.ComposedOf between service-instance and pnf) (ec=ERR.5.4.6140)\"\n\n- Pnf P1 without connection to any service exists in AAI -> Send a request with pnf P1 and service S1 -> P1 is connected to S1 in AAI",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3699,
        "name": "Joanna Jeremicz",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "joanna.jeremicz@nokia.com",
        "username": "joannajeremicz"
      },
      "updated": "2020-01-28 10:42:00.000000000",
